ial and European countries. It discusses politics and practices in education, race, religion and migration that have left schools and universities failing to engage with a multiracial and multicultural society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMulticultural educationzGreat Britain. 0aRace relationsxStudy and teachingzGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831111966880 cprintz978144734584840uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447345831?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447345831423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447345831/original  a978-3-11-119668-8  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles